  "time_ut": 1658981699,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dd0\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dcf \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0d87\u0dc3\u0dc5 \u0db8\u0d82\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0d87\u0dbb\u0db9\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Esala festival starts tomorrow without Raja of Nandungamuwa",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Pradip Nilanga Dela of Vana Diyawadana Nilame says that the cup planting ceremony for the historical Esala Perahara festival in Kandy will be held at the four great temples on the auspicious moment of July 29 at 3:30 am.",
        "He said that the cup planting ceremony will be held at the four great temples of Kandy namely Natha, Vishnu, Kataragama and Pattini at the auspicious time of 3.03 am on the 29th.",
        "After the planting of cups in the four great temples, five internal Peraharas will be held, after which the Kandy Esala Perahara festival will be held, starting the tour and the first Kumbal Perahara will begin on the second day of August.",
        "2022, after visiting Kumbal Perahera from the second to the sixth of August, the Randoli Perahara will start from the seventh of August. This year, the first Randoli Perahara will visit the streets on the seventh of August.",
        "The final Randoli Maha Perahara Nikini Pun Poho day falls on the 11th of August, after the street tour at night, the next day morning at Diyakapana Port in Gatambe, the water cutting festival is held.",
        "Mr. Dela Bandara said that this time the Kandy Esala Perahara festival will end after visiting Perahara in the afternoon. After three years, this year's Esala Perahera festival with public participation will be special.",
        "As soon as the Kandy Esala festival is mentioned, the Raja Hastiya of Nandungamu is something that draws the attention of many people. The Raja of Nandungamuwe is the elephant who has tusked the most number of times. However, Raja passed away on March 7th."
      ],
